eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon

Packages that use eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.datagenerator   
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.jaxb   
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.description Provides classes: to describe specimens, observations or taxa, to associate other factual informations to specimens, observations or taxa (including distribution), to support identification by means of keys. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.name Provides classes for nomenclature and typification. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.occurrence Provides classes for specimens, collections and field observations. 
eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon Provides classes for taxonomy including synonymy and concept synonymy. 
 

Classes in eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon used by eu.etaxonomy.cdm.datagenerator
Taxon
          The class for "accepted/correct" taxa (only these taxa according to the opinion of the reference can build a taxonomic tree).
 

Classes in eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon used by eu.etaxonomy.cdm.jaxb
Synonym
          The class for synonyms: these are taxa the taxon names of which are not used by the reference to designate a real taxon but are mentioned as taxon names that were oder are used by some other unspecified references to designate (at least to some extent) the same particular real taxon.
Taxon
          The class for "accepted/correct" taxa (only these taxa according to the opinion of the reference can build a taxonomic tree).
TaxonBase
          The upmost (abstract) class for the use of a taxon name in a reference or within a taxonomic view/treatment either as a taxon ("accepted" respectively "correct" name) or as a (junior) synonym.

Classes in eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon used by eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.taxon
Synonym
          The class for synonyms: these are taxa the taxon names of which are not used by the reference to designate a real taxon but are mentioned as taxon names that were oder are used by some other unspecified references to designate (at least to some extent) the same particular real taxon.
SynonymRelationship
          The class representing the assignation of a synonym to an ("accepted/correct") taxon.
SynonymRelationshipType
          The class representing categories of synonym relationships (like "heterotypic synonym of").
Taxon
          The class for "accepted/correct" taxa (only these taxa according to the opinion of the reference can build a taxonomic tree).
TaxonBase
          The upmost (abstract) class for the use of a taxon name in a reference or within a taxonomic view/treatment either as a taxon ("accepted" respectively "correct" name) or as a (junior) synonym.
TaxonRelationship
          The class representing a relationship between two ("accepted/correct") taxa.
TaxonRelationshipType
          The class representing categories of taxon relationships (like "is congruent to" or "is misapplied name for").
